<item>
            <title>[SOLR-1580] Solr Configuration ignores &apos;mergeFactor&apos; parameter, always uses Lucene default</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-1580</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &apos;mergeFactor&apos; parameter in solrconfig.xml  is parsed by SolrIndexConfig but is not consulted by SolrIndexWriter. This parameter controls the number of segments that are merged at once and also controls the total number of segments allowed to accumulate in the index.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://lucene.apache.org/java/2_9_1/api/all/org/apache/lucene/index/IndexWriter.html#getMergeFactor()&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;IndexWriter.mergeFactor&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12441260">SOLR-1580</key>
            <summary>Solr Configuration ignores &apos;mergeFactor&apos; parameter, always uses Lucene default</summary>
